Organisers say that annual Plett Rage will be packed with various programmes for the youth who will be attending. CAPE TOWN Plettenberg Bay is gearing up for the annual matric rage.About 10,000 school-leavers from across the province are expected to descend on the southern Cape town starting this weekend.Organisers say the 14th annual Plett Rage will be packed with various programmes for the youth who will be attending.Co-owner Ronen Klugman says they are working around the clock ahead of the festival. There s a great sense of ownership and it s an interesting time in their lives because they are very free they have just finished school and they have this old life that they are closing the door on, and they are opening a new door a couple of months ahead of them. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)